{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place lemon zest and sugar into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>8 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter and beat <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and beat <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and beat <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add vanilla and egg and mix <nobr>1 min\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add flour and mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer dough onto a silicone bread mat or well-floured work surface and divide into 2 equal portions. Shape 1 portion into a disc and wrap in plastic wrap. Set aside.","Place remaining dough portion back into mixing bowl. Add cocoa powder and mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer onto silicone bread mat or well-floured work surface and shape into a disc. Wrap in plastic wrap and place both dough portions into refrigerator for 1 hour or until firm enough to roll.","Preheat oven to 170°C. Line 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Transfer chocolate dough onto a silicone bread mat or well-floured work surface and roll out (7 mm thickness). Using a X-shaped cookie cutter (approx. 5 cm), cut out 50 crosses and transfer onto prepared baking trays. Bake for 8-10 minutes (170°C). Allow to cool on trays for 10 minutes, then transfer onto wire racks to cool completely.","Transfer vanilla dough onto a silicone bread mat or well-floured work surface and roll out (7 mm thickness). Using a 0-shaped cookie cutter (approx. 5 cm), cut out 50 noughts and transfer onto prepared baking trays. Bake for 8-10 minutes (170°C) or until lightly golden. Allow to cool on trays for 10 minutes before transferring onto wire racks to cool completely.","Draw a noughts and crosses game board onto the front of a cloth or paper bag. Place 5 noughts and 5 crosses into each bag and serve as a party favour."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 pieces lemon zest (1 x 4 cm), no white pith","130 g sugar","220 g unsalted butter, softened","2 tsp natural vanilla extract","1 egg","350 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","2 tbsp cocoa powder"]}],"id":"r140073","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-wjMYW_NMETs\/XZWp2KVg0DI\/AAAAAAAAfP4\/Coj4N7-8iis-IT0DvdSdGFfB1FChVb5XQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_7VPvR0aCcE_LcEzv.png","title":"Noughts and crosses","publishedAt":"2017-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5.1 g","fat":"19.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"38.6 g","calories":"1472 kJ \/ 350 kcal"},"usefulItems":"silicone bread mat, plastic wrap, 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, alphabet cookie cutters, rolling pin, wire rack, 2 baking trays, cloth or paper bag, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["<strong><\/strong>To freeze biscuit dough, simply wrap in plastic wrap and place into freezer. Dough can be frozen for up to 1 month. Remove from freezer 1-2 hours before rolling and baking.","<strong>Gluten free noughts and crosses:<\/strong> To make gluten free biscuits, replace plain flour with 350 g gluten free plain flour."],"basicInfo":["easy","1h","2h 45m","10 portions"]}